To solve this problem, we need to follow these steps:

Step 1: Expand the expressions on the left-hand side of the first three equations.
\begin{align*}
\left( 49 + ab \right) \left( a + b \right) &= 49a + 49b + a^2b + ab^2 \\
\left( 81 + bc \right) \left( b + c \right) &= 81b + 81c + b^2c + bc^2 \\
\left( 121 + cd \right) \left( c + d \right) &= 121c + 121d + c^2d + cd^2
\end{align*}

Step 2: Equate the coefficients of the like terms on both sides of the equations.
From the first equation:
\begin{align*}
49a + 49b &= 81a + 25b \\
\implies a &= 4b
\end{align*}
From the second equation:
\begin{align*}
81b + 81c &= 121b + 49c \\
\implies b &= 4c
\end{align*}
From the third equation:
\begin{align*}
121c + 121d &= 169c + 81d \\
\implies c &= 4d
\end{align*}

Step 3: Substitute the expressions for $a$, $b$, and $c$ in terms of $d$ into the fourth equation.
\begin{align*}
a + b + c + d &= 12 \\
4d + 4(4d) + (4d) + d &= 12 \\
25d &= 12 \\
d &= \frac{12}{25}
\end{align*}

Step 4: Given that $d = m - \sqrt{n}$, we can substitute this expression into the equation $d = 12/25$.
\begin{align*}
m - \sqrt{n} &= \frac{12}{25} \\
25m - 25\sqrt{n} &= 12 \\
25\sqrt{n} &= 25m - 12
\end{align*}
